The paper focuses on automated software maintenance and refactoring, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The tool described in the paper performs various refactorings, which is a topic of interest in programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of metrics to measure the impact of the refactorings, which is related to software design (cs.SD) sub-category. The search-based optimization algorithms used in the tool are a form of machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of multi-objective search techniques, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
